[0m[49m[39m  27, 164[0m:[39m[49m > **Curious how this looks in Python?** The pseudocode above covers the concepts. If you'd like to see sample Python code that demonstrates these patterns using boto3, check out the [Python Example](chapter11.10-python-example). It walks through each step with inline comments and notes on what you'd need to change for a real deployment.
[0m[49m[39m  28, 165[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     166[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```pseudocode
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     167[0m:[38;5;10m[49m STEP 1: Load and version IRB-approved trial corpus and eligibility rules
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     168[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   - Retrieve trial-context from DynamoDB by trial_id
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     169[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   - Verify trial-state is OPEN_FOR_ENROLLMENT
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     170[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   - If trial closed or paused: return TRIAL_CLOSED_OR_PAUSED disposition
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     171[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   - Snapshot trial-context-version for mid-conversation amendment detection
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     172[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   - Load eligibility-rule definitions (per-criterion: category, evaluation logic,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     173[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     clinical-leadership owner, IRB-review version)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     174[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     175[0m:[38;5;10m[49m STEP 2: Track trial-state and IRB-amendment status
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     176[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   - On every conversation turn: re-fetch trial-state, compare against snapshot
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     177[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   - If material amendment detected: branch to IRB-approved re-disclosure flow
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     178[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   - If non-material amendment: continue on snapshot, stamp version-history
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     179[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   - If trial transitions to PAUSED or CLOSED mid-conversation: route to
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     180[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     appropriate closure flow
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     181[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     182[0m:[38;5;10m[49m STEP 3: Receive conversation turn with input safety and context loading
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     183[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   - Run continuous emergency screening (regex patterns + ML classifier)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     184[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   - If emergency detected: route to 911/988/institutional crisis line,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     185[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     emit EMERGENCY_ROUTED disposition, halt recruitment conversation
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     186[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   - Run prompt-injection detection
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     187[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   - Run out-of-scope classification (clinical advice, trial recommendation,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     188[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     benefits quote, prescription request)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     189[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   - If out-of-scope: route to appropriate alternative pathway
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     190[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   - Classify identity posture (adult-self, parent-guardian, surrogate)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     191[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   - Load trial context: IRB-approved corpus, FAQ corpus, eligibility criteria
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     192[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   - On first turn: deliver required IRB disclosures
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     193[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     194[0m:[38;5;10m[49m STEP 4: Run agent tool-use loop with IRB-citation discipline
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     195[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   - Construct system prompt with: trial context, population posture,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     196[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     language preference, conversation history, tool definitions
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     197[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   - Submit to Bedrock Agent (or custom orchestration loop)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     198[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   - Agent produces tool calls: trial_context_retrieve, recruitment_faq_retrieve,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     199[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     eligibility_criterion_evaluate, prescreen_capture, etc.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     200[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   - Enforce citation-coverage floor: every trial-specific assertion must cite
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     201[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     an IRB-approved source document
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     202[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   - If question falls outside IRB-approved FAQ: route to coordinator rather
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     203[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     than improvise
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     204[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     205[0m:[38;5;10m[49m STEP 5: Execute conversational eligibility prescreen
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     206[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   - For each criterion the conversation has addressed:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     207[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - SIMPLE_STRUCTURED: evaluate deterministically from patient response
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     208[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - COMPLEX_STRUCTURED: capture as patient-reported, tag for coordinator
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     209[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       verification
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     210[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - CLINICAL_JUDGMENT: flag for coordinator review, capture patient report
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     211[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       as input not determination
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     212[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - VERIFICATION_ONLY: capture, defer to coordinator
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     213[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   - Compute overall disposition:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     214[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - Any hard exclusion met -> DISQUALIFIED
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     215[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - All simple criteria met, complex/clinical pending -> UNCERTAIN_PENDING
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     216[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - High confidence across simple and complex -> LIKELY_ELIGIBLE
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     217[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - Patient declined -> DECLINED_BY_PATIENT
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     218[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     219[0m:[38;5;10m[49m STEP 6: Run output safety with IRB-language faithfulness verification
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     220[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   - Apply Bedrock Guardrail (recommendation-language, trial-comparison,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     221[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     clinical-decision filters)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     222[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   - Verify IRB-language faithfulness: each trial-specific statement cross-
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     223[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     referenced against IRB-approved corpus
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     224[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   - Verify interest-vs-consent distinction: no output implies consent
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     225[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     has been collected
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     226[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   - Verify required disclosures were surfaced (first turn)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     227[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   - If violations detected: regenerate with corrected constraints or
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     228[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     substitute safe template
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     229[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     230[0m:[38;5;10m[49m STEP 7: Orchestrate coordinator handoff with throughput control
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     231[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   - Check coordinator-queue depth against throughput floor
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     232[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   - If queue depth exceeds floor: deliver "coordinator-team-busy" flow
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     233[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     with trial materials and timing expectation
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     234[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   - If within floor: capture patient's preferred follow-up channel and time,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     235[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     generate structured prescreen summary, enqueue handoff in SQS,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     236[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     confirm handoff arrangement with patient
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     237[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   - Emit HANDOFF_SCHEDULED event to EventBridge
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     238[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   - Route to Amazon Connect for coordinator pickup
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     239[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     240[0m:[38;5;10m[49m STEP 8: Capture per-cohort representativeness instrumentation
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     241[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   - Record funnel-stage progression: ENTERED -> DISCLOSURE_ACCEPTED ->
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     242[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     FAQ_ENGAGED -> PRESCREEN_STARTED -> PRESCREEN_COMPLETED ->
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     243[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     HANDOFF_SCHEDULED
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     244[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   - Capture demographic dimensions per IRB-approved data-collection plan
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     245[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     (patient self-report only; no demographic inference)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     246[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   - Write to representativeness store with trial_id and cohort dimensions
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     247[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   - If under-recruitment alert threshold crossed for any cohort:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     248[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     emit representativeness_alert event
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     249[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     250[0m:[38;5;10m[49m STEP 9: Persist recruitment-decision record to research-grade retention
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     251[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   - Assemble decision record: session metadata, model/prompt versions,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     252[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     IRB-content versions, tool-call audit trail, prescreen result,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     253[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     handoff disposition, timestamps
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     254[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   - Write to S3 with Object Lock (compliance mode) using the separately-
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     255[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     managed decision-record KMS key
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     256[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   - Write conversation transcript to conversation-archive bucket using the
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     257[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     separately-managed conversation-archive KMS key
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     258[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   - Retention sized to the longest applicable obligation
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     259[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     260[0m:[38;5;10m[49m STEP 10: Generate per-trial reporting and outcome correlation
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     261[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   - Aggregate per-trial funnel metrics: entry volume, prescreen-completion
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     262[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     rate, prescreen-yield by cohort, handoff volume and accept rate,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     263[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     time-to-coordinator-contact, coordinator-time-saved estimate
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     264[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   - Outcome correlation (accumulates over trial timeline): consent rate
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     265[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     per handoff, randomization rate per consent, per-cohort representation
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     266[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     vs diversity-action-plan targets
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     267[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   - Emit CloudWatch metrics for operational monitoring dashboards
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     268[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   - Emit EventBridge events for downstream reporting consumers
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     269[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
